House Resolution 926
By: Representative Huddleston of the 72nd
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Denney H. Rogers; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Denney H. Rogers has faithfully served as mayor of Ephesus, Georgia, for 35
3 years since being elected when his father, Lonnie L. Rogers, the first mayor, retired; he has
4 maintained that post in each election without opposition; and
5 WHEREAS, Denney H. Rogers has led his community in building one of the most active
6 libraries in the West Georgia Library System, a city hall that serves the more than 400
7 citizens of Ephesus, and a new fire station that serves the surrounding area; and
8 WHEREAS, Denney H. Rogers, as mayor, has led his community to pave roads, build ball
9 fields, and construct an event barn and a community center to serve the families of Ephesus
10 and the surrounding area; and
11 WHEREAS, Denney H. Rogers has led his community to develop water systems whose lines
12 extend far out of his community in several directions, has added four wells to that system,
13 paid in full for the system, and has done so while keeping his town debt-free; and
