14 WHEREAS, he continues to serve his community in developing new projects such as the
15 proposed Veteran's Park, which is in the beginning stages; and
16 WHEREAS, Denney H. Rogers serves his city, county, and state in many other ways
17 including, but not limited to, serving on the West Georgia Regional Library Board for many
18 years, in the local Lions Club, on the Soil and Water Board, with the Rolling Hills Resource
19 Conservation and Development Council with the National Resources Convention Service,
20 as well as serving on the Agribusiness Council Board of Directors; and
21 WHEREAS, Denney H. Rogers serves as a volunteer in many other areas in his community
22 including chairing a Sacred Harp singing group that meets annually in the city of Ephesus.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
24 the members of this body recognize and commend Denney H. Rogers of Ephesus for his 35
25 years of service to his town and the surrounding area.
26 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
27 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
28 Denney H. Rogers.
